Version Date: 2012-12-20Version Text: 2012-12-20Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: <p>The Student Roster Data (Dataset 8) can be merged with other student-level data by the student identification number variable "PERMSID".</p>
<p>The Teacher Roster Data (Dataset 9) can be merged with other teacher-level data by the teacher identification number variable "TEACHER_STUDY_ID".</p>
<p>Student and teacher level data can be merged by performing multiple merging steps. To merge a student-level source data file and a teacher-level data file, data users can merge the student-level file with the Student Roster Data (Dataset 8) first to obtain the teacher study identification number. Then users should determine the study period the user would like to look at (e.g., Year 1). The user should then change the name of the year-specific teacher study identification number (e.g., "TEACHER_STUDY_IDYR1") to the general teacher identification number name (i.e., "TEACHER_STUDY_ID"), and merge the file with a teacher-level data by "TEACHER_STUDY_ID".</p>;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: Users of this data are encouraged to see the Final Report for more information on the Tribes Learning Communities program. The Final Report related to this study is available from the National Criminal Justice Reference Service (NCJRS) at https://www.ncjrs.gov/app/Search/Abstracts.aspx?id=259995;Subject: Study Level Error Note, Notes: The qualitative data were coded by the research staff and are not available in their original form.; Subject: null  Type: null  Notes: Stata system file(s), rda Data file(s), sav Data file(s), stc Data file(s), tsv Data file(s), Data file(s), and electronic documentation.;
